{{wikipediapar|Transpiration}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From the French ''[[transpirer]]'', to [[perspire]], from Latin ''transpirare'', to breathe through, from ''trans'', across + ''spirare, to breathe

===Intransitive verb===
'''transpire''' ('''[[transpired]]''', '''[[transpiring]]''', '''[[transpires]]''')

#To become known.
#(''non-British'') To happen.
#Of animals, to [[perspire]].
#{{botany}}: Of plants, to give off water and waste products through the [[stoma]]ta.

====Usage note====
*The sense ''to happen'' is non-standard only in the UK but is in common usage.

====Synonyms====
*(''become known''): be [[reveal]]ed, be [[discover]]ed, [[come to light]]
*(''happen''): [[come about]], [[come to pass]], [[occur]]
*(''perspire''): [[perspire]], [[sweat]]

